## Proposed solutions

1. Re-spawn the worker for one more cycle scoped exactly to the judge's `retry_hint`: route `resetRotationNow` (`ConstructorView.fs:350`) and the index-0 case of `setPrimaryDetectorNow` (`:435`) through the existing `commitIfChanged` -- the identical one-line fix already applied to `editActive` -- so confirming reset on an already-zero element, or set-primary on the already-primary detector, pushes no empty undo step. Add a regression test in `GroupDetectorUndoTests.fs` mirroring the existing locked-axis no-op test (reset on a zero-rotation element adds zero `history.past` entries; reset on a rotated element adds exactly one), and correct `007-state-of-the-world.md:80` so the "UNIFORM" line matches the code. Re-run the full bundle gate set. Do NOT chase reuse F1-F4 or redesign the in-beam single-source-of-truth (both correctly deferred). Because the resolver cap and failure slots are spent, the operator must top up / reset the slice's per-slice failure budget before re-spawning, or the same cap will trip again on entry.

2. OR, given all seven gates are already green and the defect is a single cosmetic empty-`Ctrl+Z` step (not data loss, per the architecture critic), apply the fix by hand and close the slice without a worker cycle: edit `ConstructorView.fs:350` and `:435` to call `commitIfChanged`, add the mirror regression test, fix the SoW line 80, run the gates locally, and merge. This avoids spending another worker spawn on a one-line change the judge already specified verbatim.

3. Process note for the operator (not a slice fix): this escalation was triggered in part by the worker exit-1 crash at log line 511 consuming a failure slot unrelated to any review finding, which forced the slice's only resolver run early and left no rescue budget for the genuinely-cheap cycle-2 fix. If unrelated worker crashes should not count against the per-slice failures cap, raise that against the arc-runner failure-accounting policy so a future final slice is not escalated out of a "one cheap re-spawn away" position.

4. When the deferred live-wiring slice is opened, fold in the carried hazards the worker honestly disclosed -- the duplicate-placement / undo-desync between `project.placements` and `groups[].member.inBeam` (resolve by keying group members to placements by id, per `007-01-architecture-critic.md` Evolvability) and the dead `experiment.collections` string (`strings.json:132`). These are explicitly out of scope for the route-back above; list them here so they are not lost when the arc closes.
